-	  older laptops and ISA-bus card readers for desktop systems.  A
-	  "bridge" is the hardware inside your computer that PCMCIA cards are
-	  plugged into. If unsure, say N.
-
-config TCIC
-	tristate "Databook TCIC host bridge support"
